ISLAMABAD, Sep 15 (APP): The spokesperson for the Election Commission of Pakistan (ECP) strongly refuted reports of a meeting between Raja Riaz, the former Leader of the Opposition in the National Assembly, and the Chief Election Commissioner.
In a statement, he clarified that the former Leader of the Opposition has not expressed any desire to meet with the Chief Election Commissioner, and there is no documented evidence of such a meeting. As a result, the media reports are categorically denied.
